<subSubSection id="C3728DACC20CFFD5FF4EFBD2FC712D8F" pageId="7" pageNumber="78" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BD7DE27C20CFFD5FF4EFBD2FC712D8F" blockId="7.[151,1437,1067,1310]" pageId="7" pageNumber="78">
<emphasis id="B91C0235C20CFFD5FF4EFBD2FEF02D47" bold="true" box="[151,266,1067,1094]" pageId="7" pageNumber="78">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Small species with dark brown to shining black or black and yellow body. Anterior orbital seta often short or missing, gena narrow. Frons entirely shining. Propleural seta rather weak but distinct. Wing hyaline, narrowed in some species. For additional details see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF9A3D6C20CFFD5FD1BFB8DFC7C2D8F" author="Rozkosny, R." box="[706,902,1140,1166]" pageId="7" pageNumber="78" pagination="1 - 100" refId="ref15210" refString="Rozkosny, R. (1987) A review of the Palaearctic Sciomyzidae (Diptera). Folia Facultatis Scientiarum Naturalium Universitatis Purkynianae Brunensis, Biologia, 86, 1 - 100." type="journal article" year="1987">Rozkošný (1987)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3728DACC20CFFD5FF1EFB61FD882C1F" pageId="7" pageNumber="78" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD7DE27C20CFFD5FF1EFB61FD882C1F" blockId="7.[151,1437,1067,1310]" pageId="7" pageNumber="78">
<emphasis id="B91C0235C20CFFD5FF1EFB61FECE2DB3" bold="true" box="[199,308,1176,1202]" pageId="7" pageNumber="78">Remarks</emphasis>
. Of the 18 known species, 6 are Palearctic, and only 1 of them, 
<taxonomicName id="4C68A5A4C20CFFD5FBC5FB61FF222DD7" authority="(Hendel, 1913)" authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1913" baseAuthorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityYear="1913" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Pteromicra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leucodactyla">
<emphasis id="B91C0235C20CFFD5FBC5FB61FAC82DB3" box="[1052,1330,1176,1202]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="78">Pteromicra leucodactyla</emphasis>
(Hendel, 1913)
</taxonomicName>
[= 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF9A3D6C20CFFD5FF24FB45FE5C2DD7" author="Hendel, F." box="[253,422,1211,1238]" pageId="7" pageNumber="78" pagination="77 - 112" refId="ref14014" refString="Hendel, F. (1913 b) [H. Sauter's Formosa-Ausbeute]. Acalyptrate Musciden (Dipt.). II. Supplementa Entomologica, 2, 77 - 112." type="journal article" year="1913">Hendel, 1913b</bibRefCitation>
], is known from the Oriental Region; it also is the only species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C68A5A4C20CFFD5FBA3FB45FB032DD4" authorityName="Lioy, 1864:" authorityYear="1012" box="[1146,1273,1212,1237]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Pteromicra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91C0235C20CFFD5FBA3FB45FB032DD4" box="[1146,1273,1212,1237]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="78">Pteromicra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
recorded from 
<collectingCountry id="F37F9EB7C20CFFD5FF4EFB19FF202DFB" box="[151,218,1248,1274]" name="China" pageId="7" pageNumber="78">China</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFF9A3D6C20CFFD5FF30FB19FE762DFB" author="Knutson, L. V." box="[233,396,1248,1274]" pageId="7" pageNumber="78" pagination="168 - 172" refId="ref14047" refString="Knutson, L. V. (1977) Superfamily Sciomyzoidea, Family Sciomyzidae. In: Delfinado, M. D. &amp; Hardy, D. E. (Eds.), A Catalog of the Oriental Region. Vol. 3. Suborder Cyclorrhapha. University Press of Hawaii, Honolulu, pp. 168 - 172." type="book chapter" year="1977">Knutson 1977</bibRefCitation>
). The 
<typeStatus id="54D36085C20CFFD5FE0BFB19FDF82DFB" box="[466,514,1248,1274]" pageId="7" pageNumber="78">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<taxonomicName id="4C68A5A4C20CFFD5FD5AFB19FCD72DFB" baseAuthorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[643,813,1248,1274]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Pteromicra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leucodactyla">
<emphasis id="B91C0235C20CFFD5FD5AFB19FCD72DFB" box="[643,813,1248,1274]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="78">P. leucodactyla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is 
<collectingCountry id="F37F9EB7C20CFFD5FC97FB19FC5E2DFB" box="[846,932,1248,1274]" name="Taiwan" pageId="7" pageNumber="78">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
. We did not find any additional specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C68A5A4C20CFFD5FF4EFAFDFE562C1F" baseAuthorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[151,428,1284,1310]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Pteromicra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leucodactyla">
<emphasis id="B91C0235C20CFFD5FF4EFAFDFE562C1F" box="[151,428,1284,1310]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="78">Pteromicra leucodactyla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
during our study.
</paragraph>
